original:
Dominican art encompasses the visual and plastic arts created in the Dominican Republic. The island, known as Ayíti or Quisqueya in indigenous terms and Hispaniola in Spanish, has a rich artistic history that can be divided into three primary periods: pre-Hispanic or aboriginal Amerindian (circa 500 BC to 1500 AD), Hispanic or colonial (1502 to 1821 AD), and the national or Dominican period (1844 to present).
